com.jb.couponsystem.webservices

Class CustomerWebServices

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jb.couponsystem.webservices.CustomerWebServices

  • @RestController
public class CustomerWebServices
extends java.lang.Object
    This class operates as a web service. It contains methods that allow the customer logged in the Coupon System to obtain data from and to make changes in the database. Its methods create the instance of CustomerFacade class for the logged in customer and call it to execute its methods.
    Author:
    Alexander Zablotsky

        @CrossOrigin(origins="*")
 @RequestMapping(value="/getlogincustomer",
                method=GET)
public java.lang.String doGetLoginCustomerName(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
        This method executes the request of the logged in customer to display its companyName. It creates the instance of customerFacade class for the logged in customer using getFacade method of the present class. Then it calls getLoginCustomerName method of the created facade.
        Parameters:
        request - of the logged in customer
        Returns:
        name of the logged in customer

      • doGetCoupon

        @CrossOrigin(origins="*")
 @RequestMapping(value="/getallcoupons/{id}",
                method=GET)
public Coupon doGetCoupon(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                                                                                                                 @PathVariable(value="id")
                                                                                                                                 int id)
        This method executes the request of the logged in customer to display coupon with certain ID from the database. The ID is received as a variable with the request and is mapped in method's URL. The method creates the instance of customerFacade class for the logged in company using getFacade method of the present class. Then it calls getCoupon method of the created facade.
        Parameters:

        id - of the requested coupon
        Returns:

      • doPutCoupon

        @CrossOrigin(origins="*")
 @RequestMapping(value="/getallcoupons/{id}",
                method=PUT)
public void doPutCoupon(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                                                                                                               @PathVariable(value="id")
                                                                                                                               int id)
        This method executes the request of the logged in customer to purchase coupon with certain ID that exists in the database. The ID is received as a variable with the request and is mapped in method's URL. It creates the instance of customerFacade class for the logged in customer using getFacade method of the present class. Then it creates the coupon instance by calling getCoupon method of the created facade using the received ID. Then it calls purchaseCoupon method of the created facade which receives the created coupon instance as its signature.
        Parameters:
        request - of the logged in customer
        id - of the requested coupon
